The first table of five , then , is completed in these commandments , exhibiting a comprehensive character ; but of the special and particular laws the number is very great .
Of the second table , the first commandment is that against adulterers , under which many other commands are conveyed by implication , such as that against seducers , that against practisers of unnatural crimes , that against all who live in debauchery , that against all men who indulge in illicit and incontinent connections ;
